<head>
<title>Mutter Against Prohibition</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: September 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>AJA President Criticizes Prohibition</h1>

<p>In an interview with the New York Times News Service, John A. Mutter,
president of the 3,000-member American Judges Association, said:
"It strikes me as being incongruous that a doctor can prescribe for the
well-being of his patients narcotic drugs like morphine that are
habit-forming, but they can't prescribe marijuana."</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: N.Y. Times News Service article, "Prohibition on marijuana
prescriptions will be tested," in the September 18, 1995 <cite>News and
Observer</cite>.</p>

