<head>
<title>Alameda County Supports Medical Marijuana</title>
<!-- Place: Alameda County, California (USA) -->
<!-- Time: July 12, 1994 -->
</head>
<body>

<h1>Alameda County Supports Medical Marijuana</h1>

<p>From a posting by <a href="/revolution/by_name/N/NORML.html">NORML</a>:</p>

<p>On July 12, 1994, the
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/Alameda.html">Alameda
County</a> Board of Supervisors passed a resolution urging the
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a> state
legislature to pass -- and the Governor to sign --
Senate Bill 1364 which would reclassify marijuana from a Schedule I to a
Schedule II substance, thereby making it available for use by prescription.</p>

<p>Alameda County joins almost a dozen other locales in California as going on
record as favoring legal medical access to marijuana.</p>

