<html>

<head>
<title>The Newer Testament</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>The Newer Testament</h1>

<h2>The Book of Cool Dude</h2>

<hr>

<h3>Chapter 1</h3>

<p>In the beginning, there were no drugs. But then the god Coral, god of the
prophet Cool Dude, god of the messenger Hefe (follower of the teachings of
El Guapo), said "Wow!" and there were drugs.</p>

<p>And He saw that they were cool.</p>

<p>Then he created man and woman, to share pleasant experiences with. But the
archfiend Dr. Baddvibe, fiend of puking, dark lord of addiction, demon of
overdose, gave Bud Light to the first humans, and thus all people are born
with original uncoolness.</p>

<p>Many generations passed before the messenger Hefe (follower of the teachings
of El Guapo) was conceived and born. The messenger Hefe grew up in the town
of El Nacho, and learned the teachings of El Guapo, and became Hefe, follower
of the teachings of El Guapo.</p>

<hr>

<h3>Chapter 2</h3>

<p>And so it came to be that the messenger Hefe (follower of the teachings of
El Guapo), came into the possession of a wicked leather jacket, which attracted
the finest babes in El Nacho.</p>

<p>And the dudes of El Nacho became jealous of the wicked leather jacket
belonging to the messenger Hefe (follower of the teachings of El Guapo).
These uncool dudes plotted to sell bad acid to Hefe (follower of the teachings
of El Guapo).</p>

<p>But Hefe (follower of the teachings of El Guapo) was warned in a pipe dream
by the god Coral, god of the prophet Cool Dude, and left El Nacho on a
pilgrimage to <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ok/">Oklahoma</a>, which was
OK with the god of the prophet Cool Dude.</p>

<p>Meanwhile El Nacho was shut down by a police raid sent by the wrath of Coral
against the dudes of El Nacho, where Hefe (follower of the teachings of El
Guapo) was born.</p>

<hr>

<h3>Chapter 3</h3>

<p>Right about now you're probably wondering, "Who the hell is El Guapo?"</p>

<p>Fret no longer, for here is the story of El Guapo, teacher of the messenger
Hefe.</p>

<p>El Guapo grew up in a foreign land, a land where marijuana grew by the side
of the road, and where people complained because they had to pull the weed out
of their flower gardens.</p>

<p>One day El Guapo was sitting on a hill, after the woman who would soon bear
his first child (the first of a hundred) had left.</p>

<p>The hemp plant grew in profusion on this hill, and the god Coral, god of
the prophet Cool Dude, spoke to El Guapo through a burning bush. At least,
El Guapo thought he heard god speaking to him after he got close to that
burning plant.</p>

<p>Every day and every night for forty days and forty nights El Guapo returned
to that hill, where he had strange visions, and angels talked to him, and
told him strange tales.</p>

<p>He learned many things on that hill from the spirits that talked to him.
He learned how to tell the female plant from the male plant, how to roll the
plant in slips of paper for smoking, how to cook the plant in bread, and many
wonders even more miraculous than these.</p>

<p>When El Guapo was almost eighteen, he received a mission from God. "I am
a drifter," said El Guapo, "and I must wander the world, spreading the
knowledge I have learned."</p>

<p>So El Guapo left the land of his birth, which drafted its eighteen-year-olds
into its army. El Guapo headed north, and stayed for a while in the town of
El Nacho, birthplace of the messenger Hefe. El Guapo taught Hefe all that he
knew about the sacred plant Cannabis, and left El Nacho, because he was a
drifter. And he was flat broke.</p>

<hr>

<p>Written by the prophet Cool Dude.</p>

