<head>
<title>Record Pot Arrests</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: 1994; report released November 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Record Level of Marijuana Arrests in 1994</h1>

<p>State and local authorities in the
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/">United States</a>
made an estimated 481,098 marijuana arrests in 1994, the highest in
U.S. history, according to
the FBI ("Crime in the United States: 1994", FBI Uniform Crime Reports;
Washington, D.C.: U.S. Government Printing Office, 1995; Pp. 216-217).</p>

<p>84% of the 1994 arrests were for possession, and the remaining 16%
includes cultivation for personal use, and possession of large amounts
for personal use, in addition to arrests for sale and manufacture.</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: November 23, 1995 release from the <a
href="/revolution/by_name/M/MPP.html">Marijuana Policy Project</a>.</p>

