<head>
<title>Clark for State Senate</title>
<!-- Place: Nevada (USA) -->
<!-- Time: November 1992 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Libertarian Gets 46% in State Senate Race</h1>

<p>In 1992, Libertarian
<A href="/revolution/by_name/C/TamaraClark.html">Tamara Clark</a> won 46%
of the vote in a highly publicized race for State Senate in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nv/">Nevada</a>. Clark became
the first Libertarian endorsed for a state office by the Chamber of
Commerce, and the first Libertarian to receive the endorsement of
the Las Vegas <cite>Review-Journal</cite>, circulation 160,000, the
largest newspaper in the state.</p>

<p>Clark and several Republican candidates levied charges of fraud
after the election. Early returns showed Clark ahead 56%-44%, but
after the state election computers "had to be shut down" for an hour,
the final vote turned out to be the reverse, with Clark losing.</p>

