<head>
<title>Carole Ann Rand</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Carole Ann Rand</h1>

<p>Carole Ann Rand led the <a href="/revolution/by_name/A/ASG.html">Advocates
for Self-Government</a> as their second President, from 1990 to 1995.
Rand was the
<A href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpga/">Libertarian Party of
Georgia's</a> candiate for Governor in 1990.</p>

<p>On a personal note, in what Rand describes as the most devastating
experience of her life, Rand lost her brother, sister-in-law, niece
and grand-niece in the 1996 ValueJet airplane crash. In place of
flowers, send contributions to The Pam and Deana Gabr Memorial Fund,
Victory Christian School, 1151 Flat Shoals Road, Conyers, GA 30208.</p>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/H/SharonHarris.html">Sharon Harris</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpga/gov94.html">
	Republicans offer concessions to LP-Georgia</a></li>
</ul>

