<head>
<title>1988 LP Campaigns</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: election November 1988 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>1988 Election Results</h1>

<h2>1988 Libertarian Presidential Campaign</h2>

<p>The 1987 Libertarian national convention nominated <a
href="/revolution/by_name/P/RonPaul.html">Ron Paul</a> for
President and <a href="/revolution/by_name/M/AndreMarrou.html">Andre Marrou</a>
for Vice President. Paul had served four terms in Congress as a Republican.
Marrou had served in the
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ak/">Alaska</a> state
legislature as a Libertarian.</p>

<p>The nominating convention was spirited. Native American activist
Russell Means lost the presidential nomination to Paul.</p>

<p>The Paul/Marrou ticket was on the ballot in 46 states plus the
District of Columbia and received 432,116 votes.</p>

<hr>
<h2>Local Races</h2>

<p>By state (very incomplete list!):</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpmi/apr88.html">
	April 1988 Michigan elections:</a> Libertarian elected
	mayor of Addison</li>
</ul>

