<h1>The <a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian Party</a> of
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a></h1>

<ul>
<li><a href="sandiego.html">San Diego chapter's tips on gaining members</a>
<li>1992 - 1994: <a href="flickinger.html">Bonnie Flickinger</a> wins
	City Council seat in Moreno Valley, becomes mayor, helps repeal
	$7.5 million in taxes</li>
<li>1995 - 1996: <a href="stadium.html">San Diego Libertarians fight
	stadium bond issue</a></li>
<li>January 1996: <a href="rider.html">Libertarian appointed to
	state constitutional review commission</a></li>
<li>1996: <a href="tryon.html">Libertarian Tom Tryon campaigns for re-election
	as Calaveras County Supervisor</a></li>
<li><a href="campaign96.html">November 1996 elections</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Local chapters:</p>
<ul>
<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.scruznet.com/~grzflts/tobin.html">Libertarian
	Party of Santa Cruz</a></li>
<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://cmnsens.zoom.com/lifeline/">Alameda and
	Contra County Libertarian Party Newsletter</a></li>
<li>many more, but I haven't collected them yet ...
</ul>

