<head>
<title>Quotes on Government</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Quotes on Government</h1>

<h2>O'Rourke on Powerful Government</h2>

<p>Giving money and power to government is like giving whiskey and car
keys to teenage boys.</p>

<p>-- <a href="/revolution/by_name/O/PJORourke.html">P.J. O'Rourke</a>,
in <cite>Parliament of Whores</cite></p>

<hr>

<h2>Libertarian on Government</h2>

<p>There aren't any three branches of government. It's all government. And it
sucks.</p>

<p>- John Matonis, speaking at the 1977 Libertarian national convention. Cited
in Carol Polsgrove's "In Pursuit of 'Liberty'," <cite>The Progressive</cite>,
January 1978, 42:38-40.</p>

