<head>
<title>Dick Randolph</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Dick Randolph</h1>

<p>Dick Randolph was the first
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian</a> to win elected
office. He was elected in 1978 to the
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ak/">Alaska</a>
House of Representatives and proved instrumental
in repealing Alaska's personal state income tax.</p>

<p>Randolph ran for Governor of Alaska as a Libertarian in 1980 and polled 15%.
He switched to the Republican Party, ran again in 1982 and polled less.</p>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/history.html">
	History of the Libertarian Party</a></li>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/election/1978/">
	1978 Libertarian campaigns</a></li>
</ul>

