<!-- Place: Oregon (USA) -->
<!-- Time: November 1996 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>1996 Elections in Oregon</h1>

<P>The <a href="index.html">Libertarian Party of Oregon</a> ran the
following candidates for office in the November 1996 elections:</p>
<ul>
<li>US Senate: Paul "Stormy" Mohn: with 95% precincts reporting,
	7,128 votes (1.0%)
<li>US Representative District 1:
	<a href="/revolution/by_name/N/TonieNathan.html">Tonie Nathan</a>?
	(returns list "Johnson") with 47% precincts reporting, 2,921 (3%)
<li>US Representative District 2: ? Wise: with 91% precincts reporting,
	3,207 votes (2%)
<li>US Representative District 3: Bruce Knight 
<li>US Representative District 5: Lawrence Knight-Duquesne: with 96%
	precincts reporting, 2,761 votes (2%)
<li>Secretary of State: Jon Zimmer 
<li>State Treasurer: Marshall Monthchalin 
<li>Attorney General: Tom Cox 
</ul>

