<head>
<title>Jury Rights</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Jury Rights</h1>

<p>The reason that we have juries decide guilt and innocence is that you can't
trust the government. Juries guard against injustice in two ways: by being
disinterested parties, and by having the authority to decide guilt or
innocence regardless of the instructions of the judge or the law. This latter
right is called jury nullification and is a well-established legal
principle.</p>

<p>The <a href="/revolution/by_name/F/FIJA.html">Fully Informed Jury
Association (FIJA)</a> seeks to inform jurors of this
right, in the hopes of having unjust laws nullified.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="sentence.html">Jury can know possible sentencing</a>
<li><a href="ca_order.html">California Courts Prohibit Jury Leafletting</a>
<li><a href="regas.html">Reno FIJA Activist Arrested</a>
<li><A href="quotes/">Quotes</a></li>
</ul>

