<title>Quotes on Juries</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Quotes on Juries</h1>

<hr><h2>Jefferson on Juries</h2>

<p>[U]nder the character of jurors [the people] exercise in
person the greatest proportion of the judiciary powers.</p>

<p>-- <a href="/revolution/by_name/J/ThomasJefferson.html">Thomas Jefferson</a>,
Sixth Annual Message, December 2, 1806</p>

