<head>
<title>Health Care ID Card</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: report 1993 or 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Clinton Proposes National Health Care ID Card</h1>

<p>Reuter news service reported on August 14, 1994 (or was it 1993?) that
Bill Clinton's administration "is studying the feasibility of creating
a tamper-proof national identity card aimed in part at preventing illegal
immigrants from using government benefit programs."</p>

<p>Clinton told the <cite>Los Angeles Times</cite> the idea "ought to
be examined" and is being considered by Hillary Clinton's health care task
force. Clinton did say he opposed <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a> Governor
Pete Wilson's
proposals to deny citizenship to U.S.-born children of illegal immigrants
and deny emergency medical treatment to undocumented residents.</p>

<p>In further evidence of Clinton's internal contradictions, Clinton
acknowledged that "a lot of immigration groups and advocates have said that
any kind of identification card like that sort of smacks of Big
Brotherism."</p>

<p>Clinton always seems to get the arguments right, then say
"but ..." and contradict his argument. I suspect he internally realizes
totalitarianism is wrong but can't stand up to Hillary and other outside
pressures.</p>

