<head>
<title>East Timor</title>
<!-- Place: Timor (East Timor/Indonesia) -->
<!-- Time: war 1975 - present -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Indonesia's Genocide of East Timor</h1>

<p><a href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/EastTimor/">East Timor</a> is half of
an island located in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/Indonesia/">Indonesia</a>
about three hundred miles north of
<a href="/revolution/by_place/Oceania/Australia/">Australia</a>.
Once part of Portugal's empire, East Timor was forcibly annexed by
Indonesia in 1975. Since then, the primarily Muslim Indonesia has been
engaged in warfare against the primarily Catholic East Timorese, killing
<em>one third</em> of the population.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="invasion.html">1975: Indonesia invades East Timor</a>
<li><a href="kraras.html">1983: The "village of widows"</a>
<li><a href="dili.html">1991: Massacre at Dili</a>
<li>1993: Guerrilla leader Jose "Xanana" Gusmao arrested</li>
<li><a href="riots.html">1994, 1995: Riots in Dili and Bacau</a>
<li>May 1996: Indonesian seize bombs and guns, prevent new riots</li>
</ul>

