<head>
<title>Japanese Nuclear Terrorist?</title>
<!-- Place: New York City, New York (USA) -->
<!-- Time: unknown; report June 12, 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>U.S. Rep. Claims Terrorist Caught With Nuclear Device</h1>

<p>June 12, 1995, from Buz Osbourne (<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]">
<a href="mailto:buzo@gulf.net">buzo@gulf.net</a>):</p>

<p>Did anyone else hear [U.S. Representative] Joe Scarborough this afternoon on
WCOA's Pensacola Speaks discuss Senate Bill 735?  While discussing it, he
said that the FBI already had enough power under existing
statutes and began citing instances that the FBI had foiled or
solved terrorist attacks in this country.  After a litany of
successes Joe mentioned that the FBI had caught a <a
href="/revolution/by_place/Asia/Japan/">Japanese</a>
terrorist on the Jersey Turnpike trying to get into <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ny/NewYorkCity.html">New York
City</a> with a nuclear device.</p>

<p>Now I don't know whether this was a slip of the tongue revelation
about an incident that has heretofor been classified, but I
surely don't remember anything on the news about this incident.
Does anyone else know anything about this incident?</p>

<hr>

<p>Sources: June 13, 1995 post to pensacola.politics by Buz Osbourne.</p>

