<head>
<title>The Draft</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>The Draft</h1>

<p>... is slavery.</p>

<p>A society that requires slaves to defend itself is a society that should
be destroyed. Ours is not such a society, we need no slaves to defend our
freedom. It should be obvious, in fact, that enslaving people undermines and
destroys our freedom, not protect it.</p>

<p>You cannot be for American society and for the draft at the same time, any
more than you can be for freedom and for slavery at the same time. One opposes
the other. If you support the draft, you support doing away with the personal
freedom and responsibility that makes American society what it is. If you
support American society, there is no way to justify an institution that
works against it.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
