<head>
<title>Informant Involved with Nichols</title>
<!-- Place: meeting Decker, Michigan;
	bombing Oklahoma City, Oklahoma (USA) -->
<!-- Time: meeting December 1988;
	bombing April 19, 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>FBI Informant Talked With Nichols</h1>

<p>An FBI informant talked with James Nichols <em>in 1988</em> about blowing
up the <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ok/OklahomaCity.html">Oklahoma
City</a> federal building, according to FBI documents obtained by
a Freedom of Information request.</p>

<p>Associated Press reported that an unnamed FBI informant visited James
Nichols, brother of bombing suspect Terry Nichols, at his Decker, <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/mi/">Michigan</a>
farm in December 1988. James Nichols was upset at the U.S. government, whom
he blamed for the terrorist <a
href="/revolution/multi/war/lockerbie.html">bombing of PanAm
Flight 103</a> over <a
href="/revolution/by_place/Europe/UK/Lockerbie.html">Lockerbie</a>,
Scotland.</p>

<p>At the meeting, Nichols diagrammed the Oklahoma City federal building and
discussed how a "megabomb" could level it.</p>

<p>The FBI would not discuss why the informant visited Nichols.</p>

<p>Nichols denies the conversation ever took place.</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: June 13, 1995 AP wire story appearing in the
<a href="/revolution/by_name/N/NandO.html"><cite>NandO Times</cite></a>,
and "'Megabomb' plan linked to James Nichols," in the June 13, 1995
San Francisco <cite>Examiner</cite> (similar wire story).</p>

