<head>
<title>Bombing Site Heavily Secured</title>
<!-- Place: Oklahoma City, Oklahoma (USA) -->
<!-- Time: June 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Oklahoma Bombing Site Heavily Secured</h1>

<p>The federal government just can't seem to do anything in proportion.</p>

<p>According to a June 23, 1995 post by Bill Gorman
(<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:bj496@Cleveland.Freenet.Edu">bj496@Cleveland.Freenet.Edu</a>)
to Libernet, the feds have implemented heavy security around the
already-demolished <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ok/OklahomaCity.html">Oklahoma
City</a> federal building site.</p>

<p>Two private security organizations plus a federal police agency patrol
the site. Eight-foot high barbed-wire-topped chain-link fence surrounds the
site. There are several "perimeters" of security, the widest being several
hundreds yards out from the blast site. The inner perimeter fence is draped
with blue tarp, blocking any view of the blast site.</p>

