<head>
<title>Oklahoma City Lies</title>
<!-- Place: Oklahoma City, Oklahoma (USA) -->
<!-- Time: April 19, 1995 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Is U.S. Government Lying About Oklahoma City Bombing?</h1>

<p>A consistent rumor floating around the net is that local television
stations in <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ok/OklahomaCity.html">Oklahoma
City</a> have evidence contradicting the official
government version of the Alfred R. Murrah Federal Building <a
href="index.html">bombing</a>.</p>

<p>The rumor is probably nothing more than a "friend-of-a-friend" story.
One such post, forwarded from mailing list to mailing list, even
mentioned the television station, "KPOC-TV, situated about 10 miles
outside Oklahoma City." No such station exists.</p>

<hr>

<h2>The Video</h2>

<p>This time from <a href="/revolution/by_name/G/IanGoddard.html">Ian
Goddard</a> to the
<a href="/revolution/politics/online/libernet.html">Libernet</a>
mailing list:</p>

<ul>

<li><p>The video shows about a dozen media broadcasts aired within an hour after
the blast, in which it is unequivocally stated that the Army is now defusing
<em>three unexploded mercury bombs</em> found <em>inside</em> the building.
It was during this period that all rescue work was delayed for full two hours
immediately after the first two blasts.</p></li>

<li><p>It is clearly shown that the truck crater out in front of the building
<em>is not aligned</em> with the area of most several damage, deep
<em>within</em> the building itself. This evidence clearly <em>proves</em>
the truck was not to only source of the damage. The official gov't lie is
that there was <em>one</em> bomb.</p></li>

<li><p><em>Two</em> blasts were recoded by <em>two</em> siesmographs in the
area, one at the University of Oklahoma. The two waves, 10 seconds apart, could
not have been any other phenomena but two bombs the siesmologists
insist.</p></li>

<li><p>A woman who survived the blast said live on CNN that the gov't told
her to shut her mouth and stop asking questions about why the ATF offices
were empty prior to the bomb. She was very angry. She said essentially
"Did the ATF people have early warning? Why didn't my children have this
warning?" </p></li>

</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Identifying John Doe #2</h2>

<p><a href="/revolution/by_name/D/DavidDeming.html">David Deming</a> reported
to Libernet:</p>

<p>"About two weeks ago an Oklahoma City television station (KFOR, channel 4,
405-424-4444) reported that they had identified 'John Doe #2.'  I did not see
the report, but it was discussed extensively on local talk radio station
WKY (am 930) and also nationally on the Art Bell show ... KFOR had something
like four eyewitness reports to back up their claims. They also reported that
"John Doe #2" is an Iraqi national who served in the Gulf War for Iraq ...
the KFOR-identified "John Doe #2" owns a brown pickup truck, similar to the
vehicle seen speeding from the scene of the bombing."</p>

<p>Later, Deming mentioned another video tape effort:</p>

<p>"An independent producer in the Oklahoma City area, Chuck Allen, is
starting work on a video tape on the April 19 Oklahoma City bombing.  Anyone
with any information should contact him at: Mr. Chuck Allen, 4004 Flora Dr.,
Norman, OK  73071."</p>

<hr>

<p>Sources: June 18, 1995 posting to Libernet by Ian Goddard;
June 21 and July 17, 1995 postings to Libernet by David Deming.</p>

