<body>

<h1>March 1994 Election Results</h1>

<p>On Tuesday, March 8, 1994, there were local town elections thruout
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/">New Hampshire</a> as
well as a special election in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Goffstown.html">Goffstown</a>
 to fill the vacancy 
in the State House.  The following are the results of the Libertarian
candidates who ran in six of those races:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Andover.html">Andover</a>
 Town Selectman: incumbent Howard Wilson won with 55% of the vote;
<li><A href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Derry.html">Derry</a>
 Town Council: Cliff Berry lost with 8.8% of the vote;
<li><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Dunbarton.html">Dunbarton</a>
 Town Selectman: Scott Ives won in two-way race with 51% of the
vote;
<li><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Goffstown.html">Goffstown</a>
 State Representative: Danielle Donovan lost in three-way race
with 6.4% of the vote;
<li><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Hudson.html">Hudson</a>
 Budget Committee: John Drabinowicz won unopposed;
<li><a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Litchfield.html">Litchfield</a>
 Town Selectman: incumbent Cecil Williams won with 52% of the
vote
</ul>

<p>Election results courtesy of <a
href="/revolution/by_name/W/BillWinter.html">Bill Winter</a>, Libertarian Party 
Director of Communications.</p>

