<body>

<h1>Libertarian Appointed to Conservation Commission</h1>

<p>In February 1996,
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarian</a> Mark Tuniewicz
was appointed to the nonpartisan
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/Milford.html">Milford</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/nh/">New Hampshire</a>
Conservation Commission. In his one-year term, Tuniewicz plans
"to encourage more private, non-governmental solutions to conservation
problems, and discourage unilateral [government] intrusions in the use
of private property."</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: March 8, 1996 advisory from the Libertarian Party.</p>

