<body>

<h1>1996 Elections in Alabama</h1>

<p>The <a href="index.html">Libertarian Party of Alabama</a> ran
the following candidates in the November 1996 elections:</p>
<ul>
<li>US Senate: Mark Thornton: with 99% of precincts reporting,
	26,914 votes (1.8%)
<li>US Representative District 1: Bob Burns 
<li>US Representative District 2: Michael Probst
<li>US Representative District 3: Ralph E. Stokes: with >95% precincts
	reporting, 1,952 votes (1%)
<li>US Representative District 4: Alan Barksdale
<li>US Representative District 5: Craig Goodrich
<li>US Representative District 6:
	<a href="/revolution/by_name/H/TFranklinHarrisJr.html">T. Franklin
	Harris, Jr.</a>
<li>US Representative District 7: Ken Hager
<li>Supreme Court Justice: Mike Seibert
<li>President of Public Service Commission: Mike Chappell
<li>Constable, Mobile District 34104: Steve Fischbach
</ul>

