<head>
<title>1996 Indiana Elections</title>
<!-- Place: Indiana (USA) -->
<!-- Time: November 1996 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>1996 Elections in Indiana</h1>

<p>The <a href="index.html">Libertarian Party of Indiana</a> ran the
following candidates for office in the November 1996 elections:</p>
<ul>
<li>Governor: Steve Dillon: with 99% precincts reporting, 35,261 votes (1.7%)
<li>Superintendent of Public Instruction:
	<a href="/revolution/by_name/D/SteveDasbach.html">Steve Dasbach</a>:
	60,000+ votes (about 3.5%)
<li>US Representative District 1: Mike Krass 
<li>US Representative District 2: Paul Zimmerman 
<li>US Representative District 3: Bernie Taylor 
<li>US Representative District 4: Ken Bisson
<li>US Representative District 5: Tom Lehman
<li>US Representative District 6: Fred Peterson 
<li>US Representative District 7: Barbara Bourland
<li>US Representative District 8: Paul Hager
<li>US Representative District 9: Diane Merrium 
<li>US Representative District 10: Kurt St. Angelo: with 99% precincts
	reporting, 3,505 votes (2%)
<li>State Representative District 35: Colin Roney
<li>State Representative District 38: Joe Gravagna
<li>State Representative District 93: Dan Ferris
<li>Tippecanoe County Council: Karen D. Benson: (34%)
</ul>

<p>Interesting notes: Dasbach and a county council candidate were
endorsed by a daily newspaper in Ft. Wayne. Benson came in second,
behind the Republican winner but well ahead of the Democrat, and
was endorsed by the Lafayette newspaper.</p>

