<ul>
<li>State House District 5: Kevin Hayes: 2,843 (18%)
<li>State House District 6: Dean Cook: 1,121 votes (7%)
<li>State House District 30: Ron Bargoot: 1,939 votes (16%)
</ul>

<p>While Cook and Bargoot were long-time libertarian activists, Hayes
was unaffiliated with the party before winning a write-in campaign in
its primary. In addition, Libertarian
<a href="/revolution/by_name/P/GeorgePhillies.html">George Phillies</a>
ran for Senate as a write-in candidate.</p>

