<html>

<head>
<title>Jimmy Blake Campaign</title>
<!-- Place: Birmingham, Alabama (USA) -->
<!-- Time: November 1993 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Libertarian Joins Birmingham City Council</h1>

<p>Dr. Jimmy Blake, chair of the Libertarian Party of Alabama, ran a successful
campaign for <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/al/Birmingham.html">Birmingham</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/al/">Alabama</a>, City Council
District 3. Although the race was
nonpartisan, Blake's Libertarian affiliation was brought up both by himself and
by his opponent.</p>

<p>The larger of Birmingham's two newspapers, the <cite>News</cite>
(circulation 170,000), endorsed Blake, while the smaller, the
<cite>Post-Herald</cite>, endorsed his opponent. The <cite>News</cite> praised
Blake for his energy and cautioned him to focus on local issues, a reference to
Libertarian national platform issues brought up by Blake's opponent.</p>

<p>The final (run-off) election votes were Jimmy Blake, 2906 (55.5%), and
Virginia Volker, 2332.</p>

<hr>

<p>Postscript: In 1996, Blake decided to run for U.S. Senate as a
Republican. We will see how receptive the old party is to new ideas.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
