<html>

<head>
<title>Rebecca Wilber</title>
<!-- Place: Woodstock, New York (USA) -->
<!-- Time: November 1993 -->
</head>

<body>
<h1>First Libertarian Elected in New York</h1>

<p>Rebecca Wilber was elected to the Town Board in
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ny/Woodstock.html">Woodstock</a>,
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ny/">New York</a>, in a
four-way partisan race for two seats. Wilber ran on both the Libertarian 
and Republican tickets, and came in second with 25.2% of the total vote. Wilber
is the first Libertarian to win elected office in New York.</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: LP news releases by <a
href="/revolution/by_name/W/BillWinter.html">Bill Winter</a>,
Libertarian Party Director of Communications.</p>

