<head>
<title>Harry Browne for President</title>
<!-- Place: ??? (USA) -->
<!-- Time: 1994 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Investment Author Announces Libertarian Bid</h1>

<p><a href="/revolution/by_name/B/HarryBrowne.html">Harry Browne</a>,
best-selling author of nine books over the last two decades
and well-known investment adviser, announced in 1994 his intention to
campaign for the 1996 Libertarian Party presidential nomination.</p>

<p>In telephone conversations with national party officials, Browne outlined
his goal to "make the Libertarian Party a permanent, substantial force in
American politics." His intentions was to recruit new members for the
party and one campaign goal was to double the membership of the party by
1996.</p>

<p>One of Browne's advantages, he said, was that he could garner significant
support, including campaign financing, from outside the present membership
of the Libertarian Party. In fact, the Party and the Browne campaign
together raised over $3 million in 1996, a record for the party.</p>

<p>Winning the election is a long-shot, he admitted, but he does not concede
that it outside the realm of possibility.</p>

<p>Browne, a
<a href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/ca/">California</a> resident,
has not run for public office before and in fact previously advocated
staying out of politics.  He has not previously been a member of the
Libertarian Party or any other political party. However, his writings have
been influential in the Libertarian movement.</p>

<p>His books include <cite>You Can Profit from the Coming Monetary
Crisis</cite> and <cite>How I Found Freedom in an Unfree World</cite>.
Following libertarian tradition, Browne wrote a campaign book,
titling his <cite>Why Government Doesn't Work</cite>. The book was the
first libertarian campaign book to be distributed to the mass market.</p>

<p>Brown pledged to begin campaigning full-time in January 1995.
Campaign supporters include investment newsletter publishers and authors
Mark Skousen and Douglas Casey, and 1984 Libertarian Presidential candidate
<a href="/revolution/by_name/B/DavidBergland.html">David Bergland</a>.</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
