<html>
<head>
<title>Online LP Mentions</title>
<!-- Place: Internet -->
<!-- Time: 1996 -->
</head>

<body>

<h1>Online Mentions of the LP in '96</h1>

<p>1996 was the first year the Internet played a significant role
in presidential politics.
<a href="/revolution/by_name/L/LPUS.html">Libertarians</a> are highly
organized on the net, and managed to dominate most online polls to the
extent that Harry Browne earned the nickname "President of Cyberspace."
Online media sites that mentioned the
<a href="index.html">LP presidential campaign</a> include:</p>

<ul>
<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://allpolitics.com/candidates/">CNN AllPolitics</a>:
	Harry Browne, Richard Tompkins and Jo Jorgensen are listed
	past "candidates approved to receive matching funds" on
	the "more candidates" page

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.decision96.msn.com/cont_hm.htm">NBC News/MSN
	Decision '96</a>: LP and Browne are listed with Democrats
	and Republicans; Tompkins and Jorgensen are on "more contenders" page

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.sjmercury.com/news/politics/smart/links/index.htm">San
	Jose Mercury News/Mercury Center</a>: lists LP web site

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://server.berkeley.edu/herald/feb96/politic/presforum.htm">Internet
	Herald Generation X Political Forum</a>: includes Browne and Tompkins

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://politicsusa.com/PoliticsUSA/campaign96/candnews.html.cgi">National
	Journal and the American Political Network Politics USA</a>:
	has Lexis/Nexis articles on Browne

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.newstalk.com/gpp.html">NewTalk Television
	Position Papers</a>: includes Browne's "The Breakdown of Government"

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.c-span.org/campaign/campfram.htm">C-SPAN
	Campaign '96</a>: lists Browne

<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.linkmag.com/union/INDEPENDENT.html">Digital
	Campus Independent Links</a>: mentions LP, Browne, Tompkins,
	Doug Ohmen and Irwin Schiff

<li>George Magazine -
	<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.georgemag.com/vp/parties/index.html">Political
	Parties</a> mentions LP, <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.georgemag.com/vp/pres_election/index.html">Presidential
	Election</a> mentions Browne, Ohmen, Schiff and Tompkins
</ul>

<hr>

<p>Source: post to <img src="/images/news.gif" alt="[NEWS]"><a
	href="news:talk.politics.libertarian">talk.politics.libertarian</a>
	by Thomas Grant Edwards (<img
	src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:tedwards@Glue.umd.edu">tedwards@Glue.umd.edu</a>).</p>

