<html>

<head>
<title>Libertarians of Macomb County</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Libertarians of Macomb County, Michigan</h1>

<p>The Libertarians of Macomb County, <a
href="/revolution/by_place/NorthAmerica/USA/mi/">Michigan</a> (LMC)
are the Libertarian Party
local affiliate for that county. The LMC hosted the Libertarian Party
of Michigan's 1996 state convention.</p>

<p>The LMC is an active group, doing such things as sponsoring information
tables at gun rights rallies and supporting city council campaigns.</p>

<p>As of September 1995, the LMC's officers were (since changed):</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/V/StacyVanOast.html">Stacy Van Oast</a>,
	Chair</li>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/I/MathewIgnash.html">Mathew Ignash</a>,
	Vice Chair</li>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/V/BobVanOast.html">Bob Van Oast</a>,
	Treasurer</li>
<li><a href="/revolution/by_name/J/GailJenkins.html">Gail Jenkins</a>,
	Secretary</li>
</ul>

<p>The LMC's 1995 candidates were:</p>
<ul>
<li>Bob Toepfer, Warren city council (nonpartisan race)</li>
<li>Bill Carver, Roseville city council (nonpartisan race)</li>
</ul>

<p>From their September 1995 newsletter: "All monthly meetings of the LMC are
held in the downstairs banquet room of the Fire Escape Restaurant in downtown
Mt. Clemens at 61 N. Walnut just west of Main St. and north of Cass Ave. For
directions, call the restaurant at 468-0661. Meetings are held on the second
Wednesday of every month. Join us for cocktails and/or dinner at 6:00PM.
Business begins at 7:30PM."</p>

<p>The LMC can be reached at: P. O. Box 4, Richmond, MI  48062-0004.</p>

<hr>

<p>Source: online version of the LMC newsletter posted by Mark F. Heil
(<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:72113.1626@COMPUSERVE.COM">72113.1626@COMPUSERVE.COM</a>)
to the August 7, 1995 Libernet.</p>

