<html>
<head>
<title>George Phillies</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>George Phillies</h1>

<p>George Phillies is a libertarian activist in Massachusetts. As of
October 1995, he was chair of the Central Massachusetts Libertarian
Association. In 1996, Phillies ran for U.S. Senate in Massachusetts
as a write-in candidate.</p>

<p>Contact:</p>
<address>
87-6 Park Avenue, Worcester MA 01605<br>
voice: 508-754-1859<br>
email: <img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
	href="mailto:phillies@wpi.edu">phillies@wpi.edu</a><br>
web: <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.wpi.edu/~phillies/">http://www.wpi.edu/~phillies/</a><br>
</address>

<p>Appearances in <b>Revolution</b>:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpma/campaign96.html">
	1996 Massachusetts elections</a></li>
</ul>

