<html>
<head>
<title>Libertarian Activism: Strategy and Tactics</title>
<!-- Place: USA -->
<!-- Time: contemporary -->
</head>
<body>

<h1>Libertarian Activism: Strategy and Tactics</h1>

<p>Sometime around 1991, Libertarian activist
<a href="/revolution/by_name/I/TomIsenberg.html">Tom Isenberg</a> began
a series of tips, tactics, strategies, and case studies that became
known as "Tom's Tips" and proved invaluable to activists across
the country trying to learn how to grow their parties and run
campaigns. This web page has grown from that effort and now includes
articles from many people.</p>

<p>The premier resource for Libertarian activists is the outstanding
newsletter <cite>Libertarian Volunteer</cite>, edited by LP Communications
Director <a href="/revolution/by_name/W/BillWinter.html">Bill Winter</a>.
It is simply the best newsletter in the libertarian movement. It is
written for LP volunteers, activists, officers, and candidates. If you are
one of those, send your request to Bill Winter to get on that mailing
list.</p>

<h2>Issue Activism</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="debating.html">Debating</a></li>
<li><a href="action.html">Email action alerts</a></li>
<li><a href="faqs.html">FAQs and related resources</a></li>
<li><a href="gifts.html">Gift ideas</a></li>
<li><a href="letters.html">Letter-writing campaigns</a></li>
<li><a href="lte.html">Letters to the editor</a></li>
<li><a href="lobbying.html">Lobbying vs. officeholding</a></li>
<li><a href="vips.html">Outreach to corporate VIPs</a></li>
<li><a href="radio.html">Radio interviews</a></li>
<li><a href="hslibs.html">Ten things high school libertarians can do</a></li>
<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
	href="http://www.self-gov.org/radio.html">Radio shows
	with libertarian hosts</a></li>

</ul>

<h2>Party Activism</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="bumperstickers.html">Bumperstickers</a></li>
<li><a href="cspancoverage.html">C-SPAN coverage of your event</a></li>
<li><A href="college.html">College Libertarian Activism</a></li>
<li><a href="county.html">County LP improvements</a></li>
<li><a href="money.html">Fundraising</a></li>
<li><a href="mediakits.html">Media kits and cultivating journalists</a></li>
<li><a href="newsletters.html">Newsletter Ideas</a></li>
<li><a href="booths.html">Nolan booth procedures</a></li>
<li><a href="organizers.html">Organizers --- Recruiting & Training</a></li>
<li><a href="highschools.html">Outreach to High Schools</a></li>
<li><a href="primaries.html">Primaries vs. Conventions</a></li>
<li><a href="phone.html">Phone service for LP groups</a></li>
<li><a href="selling.html">Selling the LP</a></li>
<li><a href="speech.html">Speech: What is the LP?</a></li>
<li><a href="spokespersons.html">Spokespersons</a></li>
<li><a href="supperclubs.html">Supper clubs</a></li>
<li><a href="survey.html">Survey your prospects</a></li>
<li><strong>Case study:</strong>
	<a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpco/success.html">Libertarian
	Party of Colorado's infrastructure</a></li>
<li><strong>Case study:</strong>
	<a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lpca/sandiego.html">San Diego
	Libertarian Party's membership building</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>Campaign Activism</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="campaign.html">Campaign management</a>
<li><a href="software.html">Campaign software</a></li>
<li><a href="nurses.html">Candidate publicity: health professional
	trade magazines</a></li>
<li><a href="manuals.html">Catalog of manuals</a></li>
<li><a href="signatures.html">Signature collecting for ballot access</a></li>
<li><a href="signs.html">Signs: do-it-yourself instructions</a></li>
<li><a href="tv.html">Television advertising myths</a></li>
<li><strong>Case study:</strong>
	<a href="gunnuts.html">Gun rights activists in California</a></li>
<li><strong>Case study:</strong>
	<a href="/revolution/politics/lpus/lppa/timeline.html">Libertarian
	Party of Pennsylvania campaign planning timeline</a></li>
</ul>

