<head>
<title>TV Ads</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Television Ads</h1>

<p>From <a href="/revolution/by_name/I/TomIsenberg.html">Tom Isenberg</a>:</p>

<p>The Washington LP is thinking about doing some TV ads, probably for 
broadcast during Rush Limbaugh's TV show or during "Star Trek:TNG" 
re-runs. I've got an idea that I'd like to bounce off you folks for a 
sanity check. The basic idea is that there will be one 60-second ad 
consisting of two 30-second spots shown back-to-back. Taken together, 
the ad will attract people who respect gun rights and will consider 
drug legalization (i.e., potential libertarians.)</p>

<p>Ideally, we would create customized versions of this ad so other state 
LPs could show their own 1-800 numbers. Interested state LPs would 
share the production costs and then raise money to broadcast it in their
areas.</p>

<pre>
"GUN CONTROL"
Video 1: White text on black
Audio 1: "All those in favor of gun control, raise your hands."
Video 2: Footage of Nazi rally with stiff-armed salute.
Audio 2: "Heil!"
Video 3: White text on black
Audio 3: "All those opposed?"
Video 4: Famous photo of little Jewish boy surrendering (with arms up) 
to SS soldier.
Audio 4: marching sounds
Video 5: White text on black: "Libertarian Party 1-800..."
Audio 5:  "The Libertarian Party says we must learn from history. We 
will never compromise your right to keep and bear arms. For a free 
information kit call 1-800..."

"DRUG PROHIBITION"
 Video 1: Photo of gangsters with tommy-guns
Audio 1: (sad ragtime music) "In the 1920s, alcohol prohibition gave us 
criminal gangs and turf wars, but it didn't stop alcohol use."

Video 2: Photo of repeal poster
Audio 2: (stop music) "We soon re-legalized alcohol to protect our 
children and our neighborhoods from these gangsters."

Video 3: Photo of gangs giving hand signals
Audio 3: (rap music) "Nowadays, drug prohibition has again given us 
criminal gangs and turf wars, but again, it isn't stopping drug use."

Video 5: White text on black: Libertarian Party 1-800...
"The Libertarian Party says we must learn from history. For a free 
information kit call 1-800..."
</pre>

