<title>C-SPAN Coverage</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1><a href="index.html">Tips for Libertarian Activists</a></h1>
<h2>C-SPAN coverage of your event</h2>
<p>Last updated 10/27/94 by
<a href="/revolution/by_name/I/TomIsenberg.html">Tom Isenberg</a></p>

<p>If you have an event that you think C-SPAN should cover (debate, 
campaign speech for a statewide or Congressional race, conference, 
etc.) give their assignment desk a call: 202-626-7979.</p>

<p>C-SPAN has been very friendly to Libertarians, they've covered speeches 
by Libertarian candidates, the LP Convention, and other things.  If 
your campus group wants to sponsor an academic panel forum (or debate 
or lecture) on some libertarian issue, this would be an ideal way to 
get coverage.</p>

<p>C-SPAN can be reached on email at <img src="/images/mail.gif"
alt="[EMAIL]"><a href="mailto:c-spanviewr@aol.com">c-spanviewr@aol.com</a>.</p>

