</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head>
<title>Campaign Software</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1><a href="index.html">Tips for Libertarian Activists</a></h1>
<h2>Campaign Software</h2>
<p>Last updated 1/25/97 by
<a href="/revolution/by_name/G/KenGaillot.html">Ken Gaillot</a></p>

<p>A shareware program is available to help manage
political campaigns. <img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.digitals.org/digitals/pages/software.html">Precinct
Walker 3.1c</a> has three functions: a personal information manager
to keep track of contacts and the relationships between them; a
precinct manager to aid canvassing; and a "Democratic Toolkit"
containing information about recent politicians and their voting record.</p>

<p>Precinct Walker 3.1c is distributed by Digitals, but I believe
it is the same program that used to be distributed by Profile Software.</p>

<p>Although I haven't heard from anyone with experience using the
program in a campaign, Brent Jass (<img src="/images/mail.gif" alt="[EMAIL]"><a
href="mailto:bwjass@cris.com">bwjass@cris.com</a>) downloaded and
tested it. Jass said, "Someone has used version 2.6 of FoxPro to create
the program ... I'm more inclinded to try learning Access. I may
still recommend Precinct Walker to others, especially since it looks
pretty self-explanatory."</p>

<hr><p align=center><font size=-1 color="#990000">
