<head>
<title>Freedom of Expression</title>
</head>

<body>

<center><a href="http://www.eff.org/BlueRibbon/">
<img src="/revolution/sponsors/blueribbon.gif"
alt="EFF Blue Ribbon Campaign"></a></center>

<h1>Freedom of Expression</h1>

<p>One of the most fundamental of our freedoms is that summarized by the First
Amendment to the U.S. Constitution: freedom of expression.</p>

<p>Freedom of expression includes everything listed in the First Amendment --
freedom of speech, freedom of the press, freedom of religion, freedom of
petition and freedom of assembly. Unfortunately the founding fathers couldn't
see into the future, and so omitted an equally important aspect of freedom of
expression: freedom of communication in any form, including broadcast and
electronic.</p>

<p>Closely tied to freedom of expression is privacy of communication.</p>

<ul>
<li>Freedom of speech and of the press
	<ul>
	<li><a href="fbi_uc.html">FBI targets university president for
		political beliefs</a></li>
	<li><a href="housing.html">
		Feds threaten lawsuits against housing critics</a>
	<li><a href="/revolution/legal/jury/ca_order.html">
		California courts prohibit jury leafletting</a>
	<li><a href="copyright/">Copyrights</a>
	<li><a href="campaign.html">Campaign finance limits</a> are
		actually free speech limits</li>
	<li>Libertarian Party denounces proposed video game ratings in
		<img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.bradley.edu/campusorg/libertarian/lpdocs/releases/VideoGameRegulation.html">

		February 4, 1994 news release</a>
	<li><a href="freedom.html">Freedom Newspapers</a> (libertarian
		media chain)</li>
	</ul>
<li><a href="religion/">Religion</a>: cults etc.</a></li>
<li><a href="techno/">Communication technology</a>: Postal service,
broadcast, cable, telecommunications, electronic privacy, the Internet
<li><a href="sex/">Nudity, obscenity and pornography</a></li>
<li><a href="flag.html">Flag burning</a></li>
<li><img src="/images/www.gif" alt="[WWW]"><a
href="http://www.lp.org/lp/platform/foc.html">Freedom of Communication
plank</a> of the 1994 Libertarian Party Platform
<p>
<li><a href="books/">Books</a>
<li><a href="humor/">Humor</a>
<li><a href="online/">Online resources</a>
<li><a href="quotes/">Quotes</a>
</ul>

