<head>
<title>Freedom of Religion</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Freedom of Religion</h1>

<p>Libertarians support the peaceable free exercise of religion, and the
separation of church and state. (And the separation of just about everything
else and state, for that matter.) When religions attempt to legislate their
beliefs, or commit violence, they are no longer peacably exercising their
rights, but violating others' rights.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="/revolution/firearms/enforce/waco">Waco</a>: feds
	murder religious group</a></li>
<li><a href="jonestown.html">The Jonestown Massacre</a>: mass suicide</li>
<li><a href="humor/">Humor</a></li>
<li><a href="online.html">Online resources</a></li>
</ul>

